<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}}} means that a relatively rare sitaution has occurred and one can now take
advantage of it or, with regret, fail to take advantage of it.

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}no@KJ{{day^weekday^day}}nanoni@KJ{{work}}kimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Even though Sunday is precious to me, I worked.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}ii@KJ{{large^study}}ni@KJ{{enter}}ttanodakarayoku@KJ{{exertion^strong}}tsumoridesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I entered a good university with great effort, so I intend to study hard.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}}}@HI{{desuga}} can be used to politely decline an offer.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}desuga@KJ{{now^day}}ha@KJ{{busy}}shikute@KJ{{going}}kemasenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I appreciate your kind offer but I'm too busy to go there today.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}}}@HI{{desukara}} can be used to politely accept an offer.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@EM{{sekkaku}}desukara@KJ{{distant^prudence}}nakuitadakimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Since you took the trouble to bring it to me, I'll take it without hestiattion.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

